        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 4 at 3:23PM MDT by NWS Boise ID</headline>
        <description>At 323 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a gust front along a line
extending from near Hill City to near Glenns Ferry to near Lookout
Butte to near Turner Butte. Movement was east at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Areas of blowing dust reducing
visibilities.

This gust front will be near...
Deadman Flat, Twentymile Butte, King Hill, and Crows Nest Butte
around 330 PM MDT.
Bliss and Blackstone Reservoir around 340 PM MDT.
Hagerman and Flat Top Butte around 350 PM MDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
